title: Lancaster City Election Day Poll Greeting
description:
Election Day poll greeting involves volunteers stationed outside polling places to welcome voters, provide sample ballots, and offer any needed assistance or information. This friendly presence ensures that voters feel supported and informed as they exercise their right to vote.

**In local elections, where outcomes can hinge on a small number of votes, the role of poll greeters is crucial in maximizing voter turnout and ensuring a smooth voting experience.**

**Never poll greeted before?** Don't worry, we'll provide training!

### Why is Poll Greeting Important?

1. **Voter Assistance**: Poll greeters can answer last-minute questions, direct voters to the correct polling locations, and provide information on voting procedures, reducing confusion and wait times.
1. **Encouragement**: A warm welcome can boost voter morale and reinforce the importance of their participation in the democratic process.
1. **Education**: Poll greeters help ensure voters are informed about their choices before entering the polling place by distributing sample ballots and information about candidates or issues.

### Frequently Asked Questions

**What exactly is Poll Greeting?** Poll Greeters are the friendly faces you see outside your polling place who distribute sample ballots and answer questions.

**What do I need to bring?** We recommend wearing comfortable shoes and weather appropriate clothing, and bringing a charged phone to help look up information for voters if they have questions. Optionally, you can bring a chair, table, or pop-up tent; a speaker to play appropriate music (be weary you don't play music too loudly); and snacks to hand out to voters.

**What is provided to Poll Greeters?** We'll provide all of the materials and signs you need. Additionally, we provide each shift food and water.

Training content will be presented online and live and breakouts will take place in-person at PLAN's Las Vegas office.

Trainings are critical for our movement because they:

*   **Engage and recruit** more people into the freedom and democracy movement
    
*   **Educate** and onboard new activists
    
*   **Energize** large numbers of people for mobilizing and create space for local organizing and planning
    
*   **Elevate:** train higher skill activists and new and younger movement  leadership

This training is for people who love our country and understand the threat of autocracy before us, and want to do something about it. If you're moderate politically - this is your place! You are welcome and important here. If you're a pro-democracy conservative - this is your place! You are welcome and important in these trainings. If you’re progressive, this training is for you.

description:
We are in a political crisis. 

It isn't something that may happen someday, it isn't conjecture, and it isn't a theory. It is an observable fact. It is here. It is now. 

Blaming Trump would be a mistake. 

He’s the instigator, but the crisis isn’t his. 

The Republican majority has the power to stand up for constitutional rights and the rule of law. Instead, they offer support or cower in fear as the president strips residents **and, according to his statements, citizens** of their rights, blatantly ignores laws, and disregards the judiciary. 

**This leaves us with a choice: sit back and watch our slide into autocracy, or stand up and take action. **

Fixing the system will take more than an election, but the first step must be to stop the slide. This is NOT a left versus right or liberal versus conservative issue; it is a responsible versus reckless, factual versus pretend, democracy versus autocracy issue. 

**If you prefer a responsible, factual democracy, then we must start with a Democratic majority in Congress. **

So, let’s make that happen. 

In 2024, Democrats lost the House by 3 seats and just 7,309 votes total—the narrowest House majority in almost 100 years. 

**With such a narrow margin, winning the House is doable.** And one of the keys to flipping the House is on our doorstep: a Republican represents NY 17, a district that supported Harris in the last election. 

The most impactful thing we can do to halt the destructive Trump / Project 2025 agenda is to start now, to ensure sanity has a seat at the table in 2026. 

Working together, we can take a critical first step toward rebuilding democracy. **Join a gathering in White Plains to connect, commiserate, and conspire– we’ll learn more about Swing Left’s strategy and make a plan to take action together.**

description:
**Building a Culture of Online Safety for Activist Communities** 

 Kim Snyder joins us on **Wednesday, May 21st at 8 pm** for a special evening postcarding Zoom. Kim, who has previously presented about online security and privacy on two of our Marathon 24-Hour Postcarding Zooms, will discuss how to build a holistic culture of security for activist communities. Her talk will cover both digital practices and real-world considerations in light of evolving challenges to privacy and security in the world of Trump 2.0.  

Kim Snyder works in the area of technology capacity building for nonprofit organizations, and, for over 25, years has helped nonprofit staff manage the transition to a more digital and data-driven world. Kim is involved with Indivisible New Rochelle where she engages in GOTV efforts for federal, state, and local elections. She is a true believer in the efficacy of the postcard and door-knock. She is passionate about teaching cybersecurity and data privacy best practices, and in an increasingly polarized era, she believes it has never been so important to practice cyber self-defense. Watch this [2 minute video](https://mcusercontent.com/7b9e65ee75d784b2d9e54b4f1/files/623bee10-4c12-b097-90d8-975625153067/Privacy_in_Communications.mp4) on privacy. title: Marathon Dems - Resistance Lab: Organizing Training 101 [In-Person]
description:
The Resistance Lab is a series of trainings designed by Pramila Jayapal, Congresswoman from Washington State, that are developed specifically for this moment.

While this event is in-person, you can join an online version using this link: https://www.mobilize.us/pramilaforcongress/event/775585/

What is the Resistance Lab?

The Resistance Lab is a series of trainings that are developed specifically for this moment. In this first lab, we look at how non-violent movements around the world have responded to leaders who seize power in authoritarian ways and the most effective tools and tactics to utilize in these moments. We offer frameworks to understand this moment at home, and incorporate interactive conversation with others to help create community and build our resistance movement.

The Resistance Lab was developed with experts who have researched and studied democratic backsliding around the world as well as in the United States and the non-violent movements that have emerged to challenge those authoritarian leaders. We also draw from many toolkits for effective tactics and frameworks as well as from Pramila’s own background leading successful organizing movements for economic and social justice for two decades.

Our goals are to help people understand how democracies fall and the most effective resistance movements that have challenged authoritarians and dictators; to turn anger, fear and frustration into action in the short-term while also preparing for a coordinated resistance movement for the longer term; and to build community across the country that can help grow our movement. At the end of the day, we want to get people strike-ready and street-ready and make sure we protect our people, our freedoms and our democracy.

With Trump and his MAGA billionaires doubling down on their attacks on the economic livelihoods of people to thrive and on our democracy, we can’t afford to sit this moment out. This is about building real power together. And it starts with you.

title: CHOP Out Hunger, Scranton Open Hours
description:
Volunteers are essential to our mission. We simply could not make the impact we do without the help of volunteers. We work with volunteers of all backgrounds and skill levels.As a volunteer, you will be involved in a variety of activities, including but not limited to:

Preparing Bins and Bags: You will assist in organizing and filling bins and bags for the packing line, ensuring they are ready for the next step in the process. Packing Bins and Weekly Food Bags: Help pack the necessary food items into bins and weekly food bags for distribution. Breaking Down Cardboard Boxes: After items are unpacked, you will assist in breaking down and flattening cardboard boxes to keep the workspace clean and organized. Light Cleaning: Perform light cleaning tasks such as wiping down surfaces, sweeping, or tidying up the volunteer area to maintain a safe and welcoming environment. Delivery Assistance: You may also help with loading and delivering packed items to their respective destinations, ensuring that they reach those in need.

Supervision for Minors: We welcome anyone that is willing to help! Children aged 14 and under must be accompanied by a responsible adult at all times and remain under supervision throughout their entire visit. Please ensure that younger volunteers are supervised to help us maintain safety and order in the workspace.

First-time Volunteers: If this is your first time volunteering, you will be required to complete a volunteer application. This helps us keep track of our volunteers and ensures we are meeting the necessary requirements for all participants.

https://forms.gle/EiNcoQSy4DfzjxCTA

Dress Code:

Please dress comfortably and appropriately for the tasks at hand. Remember to wear sturdy, closed-toe shoes as you will be working in a warehouse environment. Open-toed shoes, sandals, or flip-flops are not permitted for safety reasons.

We look forward to having you join us and greatly appreciate your support in helping us serve the community!

title: Mic Drop for Democracy: An Evening of Storytelling to Keep Virginia Blue
description:
## Join us for an evening of stories at Robert's Westside.

On May 21, all eyes will be on the tellers taking the stage. On November 4, all eyes will be on Virginia where voters will choose a governor, lieutenant governor, attorney general and *every member* of the House of Delegates. We must hold the fragile one-seat Democratic majority in the state legislature.

Come hear from a roster of gifted tellers including [Jitesh Jaggi](https://themoth.org/storytellers/jitesh-jaggi), [Michelle D. Young](http://www.michelledyoung.com/), Samina Hadi-Tabassum, Joy Wright, Idalia Gutiérrez and [Anne McNamee Keels](https://themoth.org/storytellers/anne-mcnamee-keels).

The evening will benefit **Michael Feggans** — incumbent for the Virginia House of Delegates in District 97 — and who we were lucky to support in 2023!

Our theme is "A little help from my friends" as we give a little help to our friend in Virginia.

An incredible evening with an incredible impact. 
$30 suggested donation, with all funds raised going right to our candidate. [Donate here.](https://secure.actblue.com/donate/sd038-va-feggans-250521-greaterchi)

*Doors open at 6:30.*
*Stories start at 7.*
Seating is first come, first served.

## Your hosts

**Anne McNamee Keels** is a Chicago-based storyteller (and Teller's Nights at Robert's veteran), a Moth GrandSLAM champion, Lapsed podcast host and Race Conscious Dialogues facilitator.

**Jessica Hannah** is an interdisciplinary artist working in fiber, performance, and olfactory arts. She’s an award winning perfumer and a passionate educator.

title: Values-Based Financial Planning
description:
Do you want to make sure your values are incorporated into your retirement and other financial planning? 

Join AFSC on May 8 to learn about ways you can support AFSC and other organizations that are important to you. All ages are welcome and encouraged to attend this webinar. 

Topics include:

•	What should be part of your plan
•	Important documents to consider
•	Ways to boost your income

Speakers include: 

Crystal Thompkins is Chartered Advisor in Philanthropy® and Certified Specialist in Planned Giving with over 20 years of experience in planned giving program management, Crystal brings a depth of expertise in nonprofit and family legacy planning. Crystal most recently served as Head of Philanthropic Solutions for BNY Mellon Wealth Management leading the national strategy and thought leadership for the firm’s philanthropic businesses. Crystal is also the Principal and Founder of TrueCrystal Consulting, a philanthropic consulting firm committed to helping Black Indigenous People of Color (BIPOC) -led, BIPOC-serving organizations and allied funders create a legacy through endowment building utilizing gift planning, equity-focused governance practices, and inclusive succession planning.

Sayrah Namaste is the Program Co-Director of the American Friends Service Committee- New Mexico. In her 17 years at AFSC, she helped create a farmer training program, a farm to school program, a farm to food bank program, and incubated 3 farmer cooperatives. Sayrah was a boycott organizer for a farmworker union and has been a member of the Recuerda a Cesar Chavez Committee for 13 years, co-chairing it twice. She worked with farmers and teachers to create a School Garden Curriculum, co-wrote multiple training manuals as well as a curriculum about the farmworker movement for school children. She advocates for policies that support New Mexico’s water democracy, sustainable agriculture and healthy ecosystems.

Susan Shaw, LCSW, is a community organizer whose roots as a narrative family therapist were born out of her early activism for racial, social and economic justice. Susan co-founded several organizations including the North Bay Organizing Project (NBOP) and the Graton Day Labor Center (Centro Laboral de Graton). She has been supporting the American Friends Service Committee since 1980.

description:

title: Virtual Training: Safety Marshals for the Next Protest
description:
Are you interested in serving as a Safety Marshal for our next protest? This brief but essential 30-minute virtual training will walk you through everything you need to know to help keep our protest safe, calm, and organized.

As a Safety Marshal, you’ll serve a vital role:
🔸 Monitoring for safety hazards
🔸 Helping participants navigate the route and stay on sidewalks
🔸 Watching for counter-protesters or emergency situations
🔸 Assisting with group movement and spacing
🔸 Supporting de-escalation plans, if needed

We’ll cover protest safety best practices, key points from Indivisible’s national protest safety guidelines, what to expect at the event, how to identify and report issues, and where to go for help. You’ll also get a chance to ask questions and connect with other marshals.

Whether this is your first time volunteering or you're a seasoned organizer, this quick session will ensure you’re ready to help make our action impactful and safe for everyone.

Thank you for standing up for our freedoms and supporting your community!

title: Virtual Training: Medics for the Next Protest
description:
Are you interested in serving as a Medic for our next protest? This essential 30-minute virtual training will walk you through how to support participant well-being and safety throughout the event.

As a Medic, you’ll serve a vital role:
🔸 Offering basic first aid and comfort for minor issues
🔸 Supporting participants who feel dizzy, anxious, overheated, or unwell
🔸 Connecting folks to emergency services or Safety Marshals when needed
🔸 Helping maintain a calm, caring presence throughout the crowd
🔸 Watching for signs of physical or emotional distress

We’ll cover how to prepare, what supplies to bring, what kinds of situations you may encounter, and how to respond. No formal medical training is required—just a calm, steady presence and a desire to help others.

Whether this is your first time volunteering or you're a seasoned protest medic, this quick session will ensure you're ready to step in with care and confidence.

title: Virtual Training: Counter-Protester De-Escalators for the Next Protest
description:
Are you signed up to serve as a Counter-Protester De-Escalator for our next protest? This short but critical 30-minute virtual training will prepare you to recognize, respond to, and help de-escalate interactions with agitators and counter-protesters.

As a De-Escalator, you’ll play a key role in keeping our protest safe and focused:
🔸 Monitoring for signs of agitation or confrontation
🔸 Creating calm, non-engaging barriers between participants and agitators
🔸 Supporting trained safety leads in de-escalation tactics
🔸 Communicating quickly and effectively with marshals and organizers
🔸 Reinforcing peaceful protest values through presence and tone

We’ll review de-escalation best practices, what to expect on April 19, your responsibilities during the action, and how to coordinate with the broader safety team. There will also be time for questions and shared strategies.

Whether this is your first time in this role or you're returning with experience, this training will ensure you’re equipped and confident to support our movement and protect our people.

Thank you for helping keep our protest peaceful, powerful, and focused on freedom!
